                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Friedrich Schlaefrig</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#schlaefrigF" start="1003.557" end="x">So the buildings were sold. We were . . . we had prepared ourselves for the emigration to South Africa before we abandoned our apartment. Unfortunately nothing came from this emigration, since I was unable to obtain the 'permit' [word in English] for South Africa, in spite of all efforts of my son, who by that time was not yet naturalized. Also my daughter, could . . . who wanted to go to South Africa, was unable to go to South Africa,. We then tried to emigrate to Australia, and again we were unable to obtain the 'permit'. All attempts to emigrate, the attempts with the he . . . help of American lodges, to . . .</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="1048.743" end="x">To obtain an 'affidavit'?</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Friedrich Schlaefrig</span>:
