            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="3653.535" end="x">Yes . . .</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Friedrich Schlaefrig</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#schlaefrigF" start="3654.129" end="x">. . . the stairway to the first floor [corresponds to second floor in U.S.A.], because my room was at the first floor, the room of my wife on the ground floor [?]. We then . . . afterwards . . . in the spring of 1945, the inhabitants of <a class="placename" href="#vothC110" type="camp">Theresienstadt</a> were . . . were screened. The <a class="term" href="#vothG_gestapo">Gestapo</a> made a classification, and took note of prominent individuals. And these prominent individuals were granted somewhat better living conditions. So that the people who were put in the class of the prominent were given usually a room for two, so that a family of husband and wife obtained a room for two, and could live for themselves, also a better . . . a better . . .</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="3707.185" end="x">maintenance?</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
