            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#schlaefrigF" start="x" end="x">For a certain period of time . . . the over-aged were sent to Poland . . . In early . . . in the early period; for instance, take my transport-all people who were over seventy-five years old were 'simply' taken, transported further to Poland, where they probably perished, or were simply gas-killed within the shortest time. In the case of other transports, certain age groups were taken according to another principle. Say . . . up to sixty-five for example . . .</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
